# Group Security
To access our API, partner has to obtain *access token* first; this token is a string of arbitrary length (30+ chars) and it has to be included in HTTP header to every request to API. This section describes way to obtain valid access token and use it to access protected resources.

- to obtain access token, use `/authentication/v1/partner` resource with appropriate parameters (see the [`/authentication/v1/partner` resource documentation](#reference/security/login-partner))

- access token should be present in every request using request header `Authorization`, with type `Bearer`. If partner's access token has value `secret_token`, it should be specified as follows:

`Authorization: Bearer secret_token`

So the real example using curl will look like:

```
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer secret_token" https://api.homecredit.cz/financing/v2/applications
```

- access token has limited time validity (for 2 hours). After it is expired, partner has to obtain new one using `/authentication/v1/partner` resource.

- if partner fails to specify access token, he will receive `401 Unauthorized` error and following response body:

```
{
   "error_description": "The access token is missing",
   "error": "invalid_request"
}
```

- if partner provides invalid access token, he will receive `401 Unauthorized` error and following response body:

```
{
    "error_description":"The access token is invalid or has expired",
    "error":"invalid_token"
}
```

> IMPORTANT NOTE: Partner must keep his access token and login credentials safe. Login credentials nor access token should NEVER put into client page. If partner plans to integrate API calls in client flow without submitting the page to server, partner should implement REST endpoint bound to partner's shopping basket session, that will be used as a proxy to call HC API.

> NEVER transfer access token nor login credentials over plain HTTP. Such requests will be refused.

## Login partner [/authentication/v1/partner]

### Login partner [POST]
Partner authenticate himself and obtain acces token

+ Request (application/json; charset=utf-8)
    + Attributes (PartnerLogin)


+ Response 200(application/json; charset=utf-8)

        Partner acces token issued

    + Attributes (PartnerLoginResult)


+ Response 400(application/json; charset=utf-8)

        Unable to authenticate partner

    + Attributes (Errors)


# Group Application resources
Services that allow the processing of *application* during its whole lifecycle.

## Create application [/financing/v2/applications]
The elementary flow starts when the customer either wants to use one of the Home Credit's payment method for financing his purchase made in partner e-shop or is interested in some Home Credit's product.


Use `/financing/v2/applications` resource with the properly filled request that contains at least the following data
- The financed subject of the application (purchase of goods or cash)
- Context information necessary for the continuation and completion of the process
  - Channel type (always `ONLINE`)
  - Channel data

If the request was successfully processed, partner receives HTTP status code 201 and `Application` object with at least the following information in the response:
- Application unique ID
- Application status

Before new application is created system checks if the application is not **duplicate**. Application is considered duplicate if the request contains `ApplicationRequest.customer.identificationNumber` and application of customer with the same identification number already exists. If the request is considered **duplicate** following will happen:
  - if the previous `Application` is canceled (`Application.status = CANCELLED`), the new `Application` is created and partner receives new `applicationId`. Response HTTP status code is 201
  - if previous `Application` was just created (i.e. without any recorded action by a client), new `Application` is not created, partner receives `applicationId` of previously created application. Response HTTP status code is 200 ("double-click protection")
  - if previous `Application` is already in the application process, partner receives HTTP status code 422 with error code `DUPLICATE_APPLICATION`



In case of an error, partner receives one of the following results:
| Status code | Code                   | Explanation                                                                     |
| ---         | ---                    | ---                                                                             |
| 400         | INVALID_REQUEST        | Request was not well-formatted (malformed request syntax, size too large, etc.) |
| 422         | UNPROCESSABLE          | Request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to semantic errors    |
| 422         | DUPLICATE_ORDER_NUMBER | Creating of Application with duplicated Order number is not allowed             |
| 500         | INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR  | Unexpected condition was encountered and no more specific message is suitable   |


### Create application [POST]
Create a new *application*

+ Request Example_VALID_REQUEST (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
    + Attributes (ApplicationRequest)

+ Response 201(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

        Application was created

    + Attributes (ApplicationBase)


+ Request Example_REPEATED_VALID_REQUEST (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
    + Attributes (ApplicationRequest)

+ Response 200(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

        Application was created in the past (nothing changed)

    + Attributes (ApplicationBase)


+ Request Example_BAD_REQUEST (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
    + Attributes (ApplicationRequest)
        + `financedSubject` (FinancedSubjectBase)
            + `type`: `INVALID_TYPE` (enum, required) - Type of financed subject
                + `CASH`

+ Response 400(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

        There was an error processing request - invalid financedSubject.type

    + Attributes (Errors)


## Process result of single application [/financing/v2/applications/{applicationId}/results]
Partner may use resource `/financing/v2/applications/{applicationId}/results` to check the final state of single partner's application.

If the request was successfully processed, partner receives HTTP status code 200.

In other cases, partner receives one of the following errors:
  | Status code | Code                  | Explanation                                                                      |
  | ---         | ---                   | ---                                                                              |
  | 400         | INVALID_REQUEST       | Request was not well formatted (malformed request syntax, size too large, etc.)  |
  | 500         | INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR | Unexpected condition was encountered and no more specific message is suitable    |

  + Parameters
      + applicationId (string, optional, `123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426655440000`) - Primary identifier of the application.

### Get result of application process [GET]

+ Response 200(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    + Attributes (ApplicationResult)


+ Response 400(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    + Attributes (Errors)


## Process result of group of applications [/financing/v2/applications/results{?createdFrom,createdTo,onlyFinished}]
Partner may use resource `/financing/v2/applications/results` to check the final state of many partner's applications. Partner MAY fill in other search attributes. All applications matching the search criteria are returned in the response. There are 3 search attributes:
+ `createdFrom` - Search attribute for date of creation of application. Only applications created on or after that date will be included in the result. If not provided, 7 days before the actual date is used.
+ `createdTo` - Search attribute for date of creation of application. Only applications created on or before that date will be included in the result. If not provided, the actual date is used.
+ `onlyFinished` - Search attribute for the inclusion of finished applications only. If not provided, `false` is used.

If the request was successfully processed, partner receives HTTP status code 200.

In other cases, partner receives one of the following errors:
  | Status code | Code                  | Explanation                                                                      |
  | ---         | ---                   | ---                                                                              |
  | 400         | INVALID_REQUEST       | Request was not well formatted (malformed request syntax, size too large, etc.)  |
  | 500         | INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR | Unexpected condition was encountered and no more specific message is suitable    |

+ Parameters
      + createdFrom (string, optional, `2020-01-10`) - Search attribute for date of creation of application. Only applications created on or after that date will be included in the result. If not provided, 7 days before the actual date is used.
      + createdTo (string, optional, `2020-01-12`) - Search attribute for date of creation of application. Only applications created on or before that date will be included in the result. If not provided, the actual date is used.
      + onlyFinished (boolean, optional, `true`) - Search attribute for the inclusion of finished applications only. If not provided, `false` is used.

### Get process results of group of applications [GET]

+ Response 200(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    + Attributes (GetApplicationsResults)


+ Response 400(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    + Attributes (Errors)


# Group Calculation resources

## Financing offers [/v2/financedSubject/financing/offers]
Partner uses this resource to calculate the appropriate product. To perform the calculation, it is necessary to provide at least the following data:
- the amount the client wants to borrow
- financed subject
- method of financing

The partner can choose from which product set the products will be calculated. If none is provided, the default product set for the selected financing method is used.
If the client has already chosen the product or the amount of the installment that he would like to repay, he can also state this fact.

The response returns a collection of products that meet the input, for each product returns the amount of the credit amount, a set of financial parameters (minimum installment, interest rate, etc.) and for variable products several examples of repayment with different installments.

One product is labeled as favourite product which is the most suitable for the client.

Possible error codes explanation:
| Status code | Code                | Explanation                                                                     |
| ---         | ---                 | ---                                                                             |
| 400         | INVALID_REQUEST     | Request was not well formatted (malformed request syntax, size too large, etc.) |
| 500         | FAILURE             | Internal failure                                                                |

### Calculate offers [POST]

+ Request Valid (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
  + Attributes (CalculateOffersRequest)

+ Response 200 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
calculateOffers
    + Attributes (CalculateOffersResponse)


+ Response 400(application/json;charset=UTF-8)
            Error in processing request
    + Attributes (Errors)


# Group Scoring resources
Services that allow partners to find out a probability of *application's* approval.

## Precheck [/financing/v2/scorings/precheck]
Simple operation for customer preliminary scoring. Returns suitability of a particular customer for financing services. It is best suitable for identifying clients who will probably be rejected. Take into account that positive recommendation can not guarantee customer's approval (it is not the main scoring) as the result is based on only a few elementary pieces of information about the customer.

The resource has to be called with a valid access token (see the [Security section](#reference/security)) from partner's server.

Possible error codes explanation:
| Status code | Code                | Explanation                                                                     |
| ---         | ---                 | ---                                                                             |
| 400         | INVALID_REQUEST     | Request was not well formatted (malformed request syntax, size too large, etc.) |
| 500         | FAILURE             | Internal failure                                                                |

### Run precheck [POST]

+ Request (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
    + Attributes (PrecheckRequest)


+ Response 200(application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    + Attributes (PrecheckResult)


+ Response 400(application/json;charset=UTF-8)
        Error in processing request

    + Attributes (Errors)


# Group Merchantsite resources
Services that should be developed and exposed by partner to allow Home Credit asynchronously inform partner about important changes regarding particular *applications*

> **ATTENTION:** This set of APIs should be developed by the partner and accept calls specified below.
This option is an alternative to `GET /financing/v2/applications/results`. Any or both of these options may be used.
-->


## Application notification [/partner/notification/endpoint]
This resource is used to inform partner about important changes within particular *application*. Namely in following situations:

| Trigger                                                             | Corresponding `Application.status` | Corresponding `Application.financedSubject.cash.status`  |
| ---                                                                 | ---                                | ---                                                      |
| Application was approved (approval process is proceeding correctly) | APPROVED                           | IN_PROCESS                                               |
| Application was rejected                                            | REJECTED                           | CANCELLED                                                |
| Application was cancelled                                           | CANCELLED                          | CANCELLED                                                |

Request is filled with at least following information:
- Application unique ID
- Application status
- Time of a triggering `Application.status` change
- Notification sequence number
- Notification dispatch time
- Hashed message (checksum) - used to verify data integrity and data authenticity


### Application notification [POST]
Notify partner about change in the application process.

+ Request (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
    + Attributes (NotificationRequest)

+ Response 204
        Notification accepted

+ Response 400 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

        Can not process changes


# Data Structures


## ApplicationRequest(object)
+ customer (ApplicationCustomer, optional) - Customer data. If known, customer data MAY be included for a smoother approval process.
+ originationContext (OriginationContextRequest, required) - Additional information about the context of financing application origination (e.g. redirect URL back to partner site)
+ financedSubject (FinancedSubjectBase, required) - Subject of financing (for example IPhone purchase, loan for 20 000 CZK ...)

## ApplicationCustomer(object)
+ `firstName`: `John` (string, optional) -  Customer first (given) name. String values longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters.
+ `lastName`: `Newborn` (string, optional) - Customer last (family) name. String values longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters.
+ `fullName`: `Ing. John Newborn, Csc.` (string, optional) - Customer full name, including academical degrees and salutation. Attribute `fullName` is parsed (and eventually shortened) into `firstName` and `lastName`; `fullName` is never returned in response. In case all three atributes are provided, `fullName` is discarded.
+ `email`: `john.newborn@country.com` (string, optional) - E-mail address of customer. MUST be valid email according to [RFC 2822](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2822).
+ `phone`: `+420777123456` (string, optional) - Phone number with country code (including leading `+`)
+ `addresses` (array[Address], fixed-type, optional) - Addresses.
+ identificationNumber: `890619/5723` (string, optional) - Client's identification number (actually birth number). MAY be filled if known. SHOULD consist only of digits and '/' character, other characters will be discarded. After this transformation string values longer than 11 characters will be shortened to 11 characters.
+ `tin`: `12333321` (string, optional) - Tax identification number (ICO). String values longer than 10 characters will be shortened to 10 characters.
+ ipAddress: `172.10.10.1` (string, optional) - IPv4 or IPv6 address of a customer.
+ fingerprintComponents (KeyValue, optional) - Fingerprints components.


## Address(object)
+ `city`: `Prague` (string, required) - City. String values longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters.
+ `streetAddress`: `Letenská` (string, required) - Street/city part. String values longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters.
+ `streetNumber`: `22` (string, required) - Street number. String values longer than 50 characters will be shortened to 50 characters.
+ `zip`: `140 00` (string, required) - Postal code. String values longer than 10 characters will be shortened to 10 characters.
+ `flags` (array[AddressFlag], fixed-type,  required) - Types of the address.

## AddressFlag(enum)
+ `PERMANENT` - Permanent residential address
+ `CONTACT` - Contact address

## FinancedSubjectBase(object)
+ type (enum, required) - Financed subject type
  + `CASH` - Loan without any specific purpose
+ cash (CashBase, required) - Information about client's financial requirements. REQUIRED for CASH type of Financed subject.

## CashBase(object)
+ amount (Amount, optional) - Preferred amount client's want to borrow. MAY be provided, if not provided, the default amount would be offered.
+ financing (CashFinancing, required) - Information about the form of financing `CASH` application (for example Close-end Loan, Revolving Loan, etc.).

## CashFinancing(object)
+ type (enum, required) - Financing type suitable for `CASH` application.
    + `LOAN_WALLET` - Revolving loan used specifically for lending money (usually not suitable for shopping purposes).
+ loanWallet (SettingsLoanWallet,  required) - Settings for `LOAN_WALLET` Financing type. REQUIRED for `LOAN_WALLET` financing type


## SettingsLoanWallet(object)
+ preferredInstallment (Amount,  optional) - Preferred installment amount client would like to pay in monthly installment to pay his loan (amount should be rounded to hundreds CZK/ 5 EUR).
OPTIONAL, if not provided, a minimum installment amount would be used.
+ productSetCode: `COCONL` (string, optional) - Product set code. If chosen product is not from default product set it is RECOMMENDED to provide code of its product set.  Invalid product set is discarded.
+ productCode: `COCONL06` (string,  optional) - Product code (obtained from calculation result).
SHOULD be valid in combination with attributes `cash.amount` and `preferredInstallment`. Invalid product is discarded and the client will choose the correct product after redirection to Home Credit's front-end application; examples of invalid settings: the product does not exist or does not support the requested credit amount.

## OriginationContextRequest(object)
+ channel (OriginationChannel, required) - Origination channel
+ precheckIds (array[string], fixed-type, optional) - Array of all precheck ids related to this application. If partner has run Precheck operation with this Client's data he SHOULD provide precheckId into this attribute. SHOULD be valid precheckId. See Precheck operations and their's response.
+ sourceId: `Cash_10_2020` (string, optional) - Identifier of source or campaign of lead origin. Partner SHOULD provide valid `sourceId`
+ extendedData (array[KeyValue], fixed-type, optional) - Additional data about application origin. List of supported `keys` for `extendedData`: `utm_source`, `utm_medium`, `utm_campaign`, `utm_term`, `utm_content`, `gclid`, `fbclid`, `url`.


## OriginationChannel(object)
+ type (enum, required) - Type of origination channel
    + `ONLINE` - Client handles the whole application himself online without any partner's employees interference (for example client's purchase in eshop)
+ online (MerchantURLs,  required) - Collection of partner's URLs used for redirection of a client back to a partner website or as a notification endpoint. REQUIRED for `ONLINE` channel type


## MerchantURLs(object)
+ approvedRedirect: `https://www.partnereshop.cz` (string, optional) - URL of the partner used for redirection of the client back to partner website after the application approval. MUST be a valid URL according to [RFC 3986](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986). URL SHOULD contain scheme (for example `https://`) otherwise some browsers will not redirect client correcly.  MUST NOT be longer than 1000 characters.
+ rejectedRedirect: `https://www.partnereshop.cz/kosik` (string, optional) - URL of the partner used for redirection of the client back to partner website after application rejection. MUST be valid URL according to [RFC 3986](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986). URL SHOULD contain scheme (for example `https://`) otherwise some browsers will not redirect client correcly. MUST NOT be longer than 1000 characters.
+ notificationEndpoint: `https://www.partnereshop.cz/order/AA234` (string, optional) - URL of the partner used as a notification endpoint for notifying partner about important updates in the application process (approval, rejection, cancellation, etc.). MUST be valid URL according to [RFC 3986](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986). URL SHOULD contain scheme (for example `https://`). MUST NOT be longer than 1000 characters.


## ApplicationBase(object)
+ id: `123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426655440000` (string,  required) - Primary identifier of the application
+ status (enum, required) - Application status
    + `CREATED` - Application process has not started yet
    + `PRESCORED` - Preliminary approved
    + `APPROVED` - Application is approved, contract signature process is in progress
    + `VERIFICATION` - Manual review of application by Home Credit employee is in progress
    + `ALTERNATIVE` - Alternative offered to client
    + `CONFIRMED` - Signed by client, contract finalization by Home Credit employee is in progress
    + `REJECTED`
    + `CANCELLED`
+ workflowSteps (array[WorkflowStep], fixed-type, optional) - Collection of currently available application process actions.


## WorkflowStep(object)
+ code (enum, required) - Workflow code
    + `REDIRECT`
+ priority: 1 (number, required) - Identifier of workflow step's priority expressed as number (lowest number means highest priority)
+ mandatory: true (boolean, required) - Available workflow step for current application in application process.
+ redirect (RedirectURL, optional) - Data for workflow step `REDIRECT`

## RedirectURL(object)
+ gatewayRedirectUrl: `https://pujcka.homecredit.cz` (string,  required) - Gateway redirect URL. Partner SHOULD redirect the client to this address for the continuation of the application approval process.


## CalculateOffersRequest (object)
+ type (enum, required) - Financed subject type
  + `CASH` - Loan without any specific purpose
+ cash (CashCalculateOffers, required) - Information about client's financial requirements. REQUIRED for `CASH` type of Financed subject.

## CashCalculateOffers (object)
+ amount (Amount, optional) - Preferred amount clients want to lend. MAY be provided; if not provided, the maximum possible amount would be offered to the client.
+ financing (CashFinancing, required) - Information about form of financing `CASH` application (for example Close-end Loan, Revolving Loan, etc.).


## CalculateOffersResponse (object)
+ type (enum, required) - Financing type suitable for CASH application.
    + `LOAN_WALLET` - Revolving loan used specifically for lending money (usually not suitable for shopping purposes).
+ loanWallet (LoanWalletOffer,  required) - Settings for `LOAN_WALLET` Financing type. REQUIRED for `LOAN_WALLET` financing type

## WalletOffer (object)
+ productCode: `HCONLESHOP` (string, required) - Product offer code
+ creditAmount (AvailableCreditAmount, required) - Available credit amount of product offer
+ calculation (CalculationDetail, required) - Financial characteristics of product offer
+ flags (array[enum], fixed-type, optional) - Additional characteristics of product offer code
  + `FAVOURITE` - Favourite product, usually the first one to offer to client

## LoanWalletOffer (WalletOffer)
+ repaymentExamples (array[RepaymentExample],fixed-type,optional) - Examples of debt repayement for flexible product with variable end (with various installments)

## AvailableCreditAmount (object)
+ type: `FIXED` (enum, required) - Credit amount can be fixed for particular amount or variable
  + `FIXED` - Fixed amount
  + `VARIABLE` - Variable amount
+ fixed (Amount, optional) - REQUIRED for `FIXED` type of credit amount
+ variable (VariableCreditAmount, optional) - REQUIRED for `VARIABLE` type of credit amount

## VariableCreditAmount (object)
+ minimum (Amount, required) - Minimal available credit amount
+ maximum (Amount, required) - Maximal available credit amount

## CalculationDetail (object)
+ installment (Amount, required) - Value of monthly installment. Approximated for product offers with variable end
+ annualInterestRate: 0.17 (number, required) - Annual interest rate
+ annualPercentageRate: 0.23 (string, required) - Annual percentage rate of loan (so-called "RPSN"/"RPMN")
+ numberOfInstallments: 12 (number, required) - Count of installments needed to repay purchased loan. Approximated for product offers with a variable end.
+ installmentFirstDate: `2021-03-20` (string, required) - Date of first installment.
+ installmentLastDate: `2022-02-20` (string, required) - Date of last installment. Approximated for product offers with a variable end.
+ predictedProvisionDate (string, required) - Predicted date of sending fund to client's account
+ amountToPay (Amount, required) - Total amount will pay for the loan (including the costs)
+ installmentDay: 20 (number, required) - Day of installment
+ legalLine: `Ilustrativní výpočet dle zákona: Výše úvěru 10 000 Kč, roční úroková sazba 14,88 %, RPSN 15,9 %, celkem zaplatíte 10 806 Kč. Jednotlivé po sobě jdoucí měsíční splátky: 957 Kč, 947 Kč, 937 Kč, 926 Kč, 916 Kč, 906 Kč, 895 Kč, 885 Kč, 875 Kč, 864 Kč, 854 Kč, 844 Kč. Splátky a částka, kterou celkem zaplatíte, jsou matematicky zaokrouhleny.` (string, required) - Legal example of repayment

## RepaymentExample(object)
+ installment (Amount, required) - Value of monthly installment.
+ numberOfInstallments: 12 (number, required) - Count of installments needed to repay purchased loan for chosen `installment` (approximated)
+ amountToPay (Amount, required) - Total amount client will pay for the loan (including the costs) for chosen `installmemt` (approximated)
+ flags (array[enum], fixed-type, optional) - Additional characteristics of example repayment
  + `FAVOURITE` - Favourite example, usually the first one to offer to client

## PrecheckRequest(object)
Precheck data.

### Properties
+ customer (ApplicationCustomer, required) - Customer data
  + `firstName`: `John` (string, optional) -  Customer first (given) name. String values longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters. One of `firstName` and `fullName` is REQUIRED.
  + `lastName`: `Newborn` (string, optional) - Customer last (family) name. String values   longer than 100 characters will be shortened to 100 characters.  One of `lastName` and `fullName` is REQUIRED.
+ financedSubject (PrecheckFinancedSubject, required) - Subject of financing (for example IPhone purchase, loan for 20 000 CZK ...)

## PrecheckFinancedSubject(object)
+ type (enum, required) - Financed subject type
  + `CASH` - Loan without any specific purpose

## PrecheckResult(object)
Precheck result.

### Properties
+ `id`: `1234` (string, optional) - Unique identifier of Precheck. Send this identificator in ApplicationRequest for a better approval rate. The Id is sometimes not provided (for example if precheck ends with a result `TIME_OUT`)
+ `recommendation`:`false`  (boolean, required) - A recommendation of whether the order should be passed to the HCO.
    true = Application is likely going to be approved.
    false = Application is likely going to be rejected.
+ `result`: `false`  (enum, required) - A detailed result of precheck.
    + `NEW_CONTRACT` - The client will likely create and sign a new contract
    + `EXISTING_CONTRACT` - The client will use an existing contract to finance his needs
    + `TIME_OUT` - Request for precheck operation have not ended at the requested time
    + `UNKNOWN` - Other reasons (for example provided client data are invalid)
+ `message`: `V HCO peněžence nemáte dostatečný limit.` (string, optional) - Custom message for customers.

## GetApplicationsResults(object)
List of all found applications.

### Properties
+ `applications` (array[ApplicationResult], fixed-type, optional) - List of applications results

## ApplicationResult(object)
Detail of result of the application approval process

### Properties
+ id: `123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426655440000` (string,  required) - Primary identifier of the application
+ `createdDate`: `2020-07-15T00:00:00+02:00` (string, required) - Date of creation of application
+ `finished`: `false`  (boolean, required) - A flag indicating whether the application has already been completed or is still in progress.
+ `result`: `SUCCESS` (enum, optional) - A detailed result of (only) finished application.
    + `SUCCESS` - Application was successfully approved
    + `REJECTED` - Application was rejected
    + `CANCELLED` - Application was cancelled


## NotificationRequest(object)
+ notificationContent (NotificationContent, required) - Content of the notification
+ sentDate: `2020-07-15T00:00:00+02:00` (string, required) - Time when notification was sent (uses [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) formatting)
+ checksum: `f61c69a259b702d564b2032e554984dec3b713ff7bdde17fcb727d403ea0d730816f46ad2bbc06a1914225d5dfba0396927dbf1b0698081814877b5486950a15` (string, required) - Message checksum - result of HMAC with SHA512 (secret key is used)

## NotificationContent(object)
+ applicationId: `123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426655440000` (string,  required) - Primary identifier of the application
+ applicationStatus: `APPROVED` (enum, required) - Status of the application
  + `CONFIRMED`
  + `CREATED`
  + `PRESCORED`
  + `APPROVED`
  + `VERIFICATION`
  + `ALTERNATIVE`
  + `REJECTED`
  + `CANCELLED`
+ cashStatus: `PROCESSING` (enum, optional) - Status of the Cash loan
  + `PROCESSING`
  + `CANCELLED`
  + `TO_PAY`
  + `PAID`
+ notificationDate: `2020-07-15T00:00:00+02:00` (string, required) - Time when notification was created (uses [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) formatting)
+ sequenceNumber: 1 (number, required) - Notification sequence number

## Error (object)
+ code: `BAD_REQUEST` (string, required) - Unique internal error code
+ message: `Bad request` (string, required) - Human readable error description (non-localized)
+ severity (enum, required)
    + `ERROR` - Critical error, execution cannot continue. This MUST be indicated also by appropriate HTTP status code
    + `WARN` - Non-critical error, execution can continue but further user interaction is advisable. This MIGHT be indicated also by appropriate HTTP status code
    + `INFO` - Information only, execution can continue without user interaction
+ attribute: `Client.addresses[1].streetNumber` (string, optional) - JSON path of request attribute that caused the error (if applicable)
+ ticketId: `UAT1:AMS:20160516-091658.450:45e4` (string, optional) - Internal ticket ID, used for error backtracking

## Errors (object)
+ errors (array[Error], fixed-type, required) - Array with errors

## Amount (object)
+ `value`: 13300 (number, required) - Amount in minor units (13300 represents 133) [ISO 4217](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)
+ `currency`: `CZK` (string, required) - Amount currency [ISO 4217](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217). Only local currency is allowed (CZK in Czech Republic and EUR in Slovakia).

## File (object)
+ `filename`: `iphone6s.jpg` (string, required) - File name.
+ One Of
    + `url`: `https://i.cdn.nrholding.net/32523771/2000/2000/iphone6s.jpg` (string, required) - File URL (full).
    + `content`: `RmlsZSBjb250ZW50cy4gwq9cXyjjg4QpXy/Crw==` (string, required) - File content (Base64 encoded, maximum size of encoded string is 500kB)


## KeyValue (object)
+ `key`: `property` (string, required) - Key
+ `value`: `value` (string, required) - Value

## BankAccount (object)
+ type (enum, required) - Account type
    + `IBAN`
    + `NATIONAL`
+ One Of
    + iban (AccountIBAN, required) - Bank account number in IBAN format
    + national (AccountNational, required) - Bank account number in national format.

## AccountIBAN (object)
+ iban: `CZ6508000000192000145399` (string, required) - Account number in IBAN format

## AccountNational (object)
+ prefix: `000000` (string, optional) - Account number prefix. For domestic accounts, this will be specified in national format.
+ accountNumber: `1235335010` (string, required) - Account number. For domestic accounts, this will be specified in national format.
+ bankCode: `3030` (string, required) - For domestic accounts, bank code in national format

## PhoneNumber (object)
+ number: `+420123456789` (string, required) - Phone number (including country code)

## Email (object)
+ address: `darth.vader@empire.sw` (string, required) - Email address


## PartnerLogin (object)
Partner login credentials

### Properties
+ `username`: `partner` (string, required) - Partner username
+ `password`: `partnerSecretPassword` (string, required) - Partner secret password

## PartnerLoginResult (object)
Authenticated partner access token

### Properties
+ `accessToken`: `TokenForPartnerTokenForPartnerTokenForPartnerTokenForPartner` (string, required) - Access token
+ `expiresIn`: 7200 (number) - Token validity remaining time (in seconds)

## TokenCodeRequest (object)
+ `grant_type` (enum, required) - Grant flow type, only `authorization_code` and `refresh_token` is supported
    + `authorization_code` - use to exchange code for access token
    + `refresh_token` - can be used to get new access token instead of forcing user to login again
+ `client_id`: `my_app_id` (string, required) - `client_id` parameter of partner's application, received at application registration
+ `client_secret`: `my_app_secret` (string, required) - `client_secret` parameter of partner's application, received at application registration
+ One Of
    + `code`: `12254a1124` (string, required) - Authorization code, received from authorization server
    + `refresh_token`: `12254a1124` (string, required) - Refresh token, received from authorization server

## TokenResponse (object)
+ `refresh_token`: `7dbadd74c434439db4fc9b2bbf8cabb3` (string, optional) - refresh token, if supported
+ `token_type`: `bearer` (string, required) - token type. Always "bearer".
+ `access_token`: `ccafe62cbce645ce95b2acce839f4acc` (string, required) - access token, to be included in API request
+ `expires_in`: 7200 (number, required) - access token validity, in seconds